<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Stock Market Discovery - Investment Simulator</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="css/styles.css">
    <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/chart.js"></script>
</head>
<body>
    <header>
        <nav>
            <div class="nav-container">
                <h1>Stock Market Discovery</h1>
                <div class="nav-right">
                    <button id="theme-toggle" class="theme-toggle" aria-label="Toggle dark mode">
                        <span class="theme-icon">ðŸŒ™</span>
                    </button>
                    <ul>
                <h1>Stock Market Discovery</h1>
                <ul>
                    <li><a href="index.html" class="active">Investment Simulator</a></li>
                    <li><a href="market.html">Market Outlook</a></li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </nav>
    </header>

    <main>
        <div class="container">
            <h2>Long-Term Investment Simulator</h2>
            <p class="description">
                Simulate the power of dollar-cost averaging (DCA) by investing a fixed amount monthly over time.
                Adjust the parameters below to see how different scenarios affect your portfolio growth.
            </p>

            <div class="simulator-container">
                <div class="inputs-section">
                    <h3>Investment Parameters</h3>

                    <div class="input-group">
                        <label for="monthly-amount">Monthly Investment (â‚¬)</label>
                        <input type="number" id="monthly-amount" value="500" min="1" step="10">
                    </div>

                    <div class="input-group">
                        <label for="annual-return">Expected Annual Return (%)</label>
                        <input type="number" id="annual-return" value="7" min="0" max="50" step="0.1">
                    </div>

                    <div class="input-group">
                        <label for="duration">Investment Duration (Years)</label>
                        <input type="number" id="duration" value="10" min="1" max="50" step="1">
                    </div>

                    <div class="input-group">
                        <label for="inflation">Inflation Rate (%)</label>
                        <input type="number" id="inflation" value="2" min="0" max="10" step="0.1">
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="results-section">
                    <h3>Results</h3>

                    <div class="results-grid">
                        <div class="result-item">
                            <div class="result-label">Total Amount Invested</div>
                            <div class="result-value" id="total-invested">â‚¬0</div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="result-item">
                            <div class="result-label">Final Portfolio Value</div>
                            <div class="result-value" id="final-value">â‚¬0</div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="result-item">
                            <div class="result-label">Total Gains</div>
                            <div class="result-value" id="total-gains">â‚¬0</div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="result-item">
                            <div class="result-label">Compound Annual Growth Rate (CAGR)</div>
                            <div class="result-value" id="cagr">0%</div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="chart-container">
                        <canvas id="growth-chart"></canvas>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="assumptions">
                <h3>Assumptions & Methodology</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Investments are made at the beginning of each month</li>
                    <li>Annual return is compounded monthly</li>
                    <li>Inflation affects the purchasing power of gains (optional)</li>
                    <li>CAGR is calculated on the nominal portfolio value</li>
                    <li>This is a simulation - actual market returns vary and past performance doesn't guarantee future results</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </main>

    <footer>
        <p>&copy; 2024 Stock Market Discovery. For educational purposes only. Not financial advice.</p>
    </footer>

    <script src="js/simulator.js"></script>
</body>
</html>